{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff7b03a7-8068-4955-b07c-fca0e178e8d4","content":"For a **Web API project**, here are the common options:\n\n### Templates\n| Framework | Command |\n|-----------|---------|\n| .NET | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| Node/Express | `npx express-generator` |\n| Python/FastAPI | `pip install fastapi` |\n\n### .NET Authentication Options (`dotnet new webapi --auth`)\n- **None** – No auth (default)\n- **Individual** – Individual user accounts (ASP.NET Identity)\n- **IndividualB2C** – Azure AD B2C\n- **SingleOrg** – Single-tenant Azure AD\n- **MultiOrg** – Multi-tenant Azure AD\n- **Windows** – Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n### Example\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\n### Other Common Auth Approaches\n- **JWT Bearer tokens** – Add via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`\n- **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** – For third-party identity providers\n- **API Keys** – Custom middleware\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8658480b-da63-40dc-964b-14deed305fc3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context) or potentially other frameworks. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to explore the codebase, since this is a general development question.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"5019:B987F:12D8F9C:153435F:6A066E7D"},"id":"a7fa8d50-d1a6-41a7-a365-7103717ac87c","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:26.739Z","parentId":"c690d98a-557e-4c57-b181-375066787b7b"}
